 \"quarantine and disinfection measures\", \"from\": 1379, \"to\": 1415}, {\"ngram\": \"aircraft\", \"from\": 1453, \"to\": 1461}, {\"ngram\": \"a focus\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1475}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hub will also regularly be disinfected in areas with high passenger traffic.\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1585, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The hub\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"areas\", \"from\": 1551, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"high passenger traffic\", \"from\": 1562, \"to\": 1584}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lee Han-kyung, the head of the Disaster and Safety Management Headquarters of the Ministry of the Interior and Safety, said: \\\"It is important to block the inflow of bedbugs in advance because it is difficult to control them once they are discovered.\", \"from\": 1587, \"to\": 1836, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1587, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"score\": 0.9992147495772956, \"rank\": 0.0006746053767453115, \"text\": \"Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Robert_E._Lee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the head\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"the Disaster and Safety Management Headquarters\", \"from\": 1614, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"the Ministry\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1677}, {\"ngram\": \"the Interior\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1693}, {\"ngram\": \"Safety\", \"from\": 1698, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"the inflow\", \"from\": 1738, \"to\": 1748}, {\"ngram\": \"bedbugs\", \"from\": 1752, \"to\": 1759}, {\"ngram\": \"advance\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1770}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Therefore, we will strengthen preemptive blocking measures starting from the airport through public-private cooperation.\\\"\", \"from\": 1837, \"to\": 1958, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"preemptive blocking measures\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1895}, {\"ngram\": \"the airport\", \"from\": 1910, \"to\": 1921}, {\"ngram\": \"public-private cooperation\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"South Korea sent 144 athletes to compete at the Olympics in Paris.\", \"from\": 1960, \"to\": 2026, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1960, \"end\": 1971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"score\": 0.9998201954111354, \"rank\": 0.00017983692198507295, \"text\": \"South Korea\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Korea\"}, {\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.999999991155164, \"rank\": 8.8449376262917e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"144 athletes\", \"from\": 1977, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 2004, \"to\": 2016}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Along with the athletes, other officials, trainers, and spectators also traveled to the French capital.\", \"from\": 2027, \"to\": 2130, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2115, \"end\": 2121, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8114291032048025, \"rank\": 0.15553117387532417, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2050}, {\"ngram\": \"other officials\", \"from\": 2052, \"to\": 2067}, {\"ngram\": \"trainers\", \"from\": 2069, \"to\": 2077}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 2083, \"to\": 2093}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris had a bedbugoutbreak in late 2023which sparked widespread media attention.\", \"from\": 2132, \"to\": 2212, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2132, \"end\": 2137, \"title\": \"http://